1
00:00:15,104 --> 00:00:16,352
(You remember Lee Seri, right?)

2
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:23,440
(Saebyeok, open the door.)

3
00:00:23,990 --> 00:00:24,990
(You're in there, right?)

4
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:17,760
=Never Forget Your Enemy=

5
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:24,542
=Episode 7=
(Nevertheless, Love)

6
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:32,383
Saebyeok!

7
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:34,886
I'm a fan of yours.

8
00:01:37,305 --> 00:01:38,139
Me?

9
00:01:38,681 --> 00:01:40,391
Are you really giving this to me?

10
00:01:41,643 --> 00:01:42,560
Thank you.

11
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:45,522
I really enjoyed your latest work.

12
00:01:45,688 --> 00:01:47,899
But it was such a small role.
I barely appeared in it.

13
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:50,443
No, you were absolutely amazing.

14
00:01:50,735 --> 00:01:52,695
I'll be looking forward
to your next project.

15
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:55,573
Thank you.

16
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:57,492
Fighting!

17
00:01:58,368 --> 00:01:58,993
Thank you.

18
00:02:02,682 --> 00:02:05,568
(Actor Yeo Saebyeok)

19
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:09,838
Saebyeok, a fan sent you a gift.

20
00:02:10,421 --> 00:02:12,715
Wow, you're getting gifts from fans now.

21
00:02:13,792 --> 00:02:15,218
What is it? Let's open it together.

22
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:17,679
I'll open it alone.

23
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:20,056
Seriously.

24
00:02:26,729 --> 00:02:27,897
Were you waiting for me?

25
00:02:29,732 --> 00:02:30,358
Yes!

26
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:31,860
Did you wait long?

27
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:34,654
You must be tired of standing here
with nowhere to sit.

28
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:37,073
No, I just got here.

29
00:02:37,365 --> 00:02:39,826
Really, I didn't wait long.

30
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:41,870
Here, please take this.

31
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:46,583
What... is this?

32
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:49,460
You always come to support me
and even write me letters,

33
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:51,796
but I feel like I never
properly thanked you.

34
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:54,465
No! You really don't
need to give me anything.

35
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:57,760
Just seeing you work so hard as an actor

36
00:02:58,845 --> 00:02:59,679
is enough for me.

37
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,431
It's really nothing.

38
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:03,766
I really wanted to say
thank you properly.

39
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:04,893
Please accept it.

40
00:03:07,228 --> 00:03:08,354
Thank you!

41
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,565
I'll support you until the end.

42
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:13,818
Oh, so if you find a better actor,
you'll go support them instead?

43
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:17,655
No! You're the coolest person
in the world to me, Saebyeok.

44
00:03:17,947 --> 00:03:19,949
Saebyeok, I think
you need to head back in.

45
00:03:20,074 --> 00:03:20,825
Okay!

46
00:03:21,659 --> 00:03:22,952
I should probably head back in.

47
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,280
Please get home safely.

48
00:03:24,495 --> 00:03:26,039
Yes! Please go ahead.

49
00:03:32,837 --> 00:03:34,589
(I'll treasure this forever.)

50
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:37,842
Ms. Seri!

51
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:39,719
- Hello.
- Hello.

52
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:43,139
Saebyeok will be on break soon,
so I thought you could say hi briefly.

53
00:03:43,392 --> 00:03:46,336
- Thank you.
- Oh, we're more grateful.

54
00:03:47,143 --> 00:03:51,272
Everyone at our company watches
the social media accounts you run.

55
00:03:52,482 --> 00:03:54,234
In fact, you've been posting updates

56
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:56,694
and promoting Saebyeok
even more actively than our PR team.

57
00:03:57,403 --> 00:03:58,488
We are truly so thankful.

58
00:03:58,488 --> 00:03:59,322
Not at all.

59
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,450
And Saebyeok is also very grateful.

60
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:04,619
Really? That's a relief.

61
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:07,247
Hello, you're here.

62
00:04:09,249 --> 00:04:10,250
What is all this?

63
00:04:11,270 --> 00:04:12,630
You didn't have to bring anything.

64
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:15,588
I thought you could
share it with the staff.

65
00:04:16,464 --> 00:04:19,300
Next time, just come
and say hello. Really.

66
00:04:20,009 --> 00:04:21,636
It's nothing much.

67
00:04:22,887 --> 00:04:23,888
How did you get here?

68
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:26,683
I took a taxi and then a bus...

69
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:28,559
It didn't take that long.

70
00:04:28,559 --> 00:04:29,936
How are you planning to go back?

71
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:32,563
I plan to take the bus from over there.

72
00:04:33,314 --> 00:04:35,650
Then, can you give her
a ride to the bus stop?

73
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:37,151
Yeah, of course.

74
00:04:37,568 --> 00:04:38,778
I'm really fine...

75
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:40,530
I'm not fine with it, so please.

76
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:42,782
Ah, but I need to head back in now.

77
00:04:43,574 --> 00:04:46,119
Okay, got it. Fighting today
as well, Saebyeok!

78
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:48,037
Yes, thank you. Please get home safely.

79
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:51,874
- Let's go.
- Yes.

80
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:18,192
Take care.

81
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:19,652
Thank you.

82
00:05:27,076 --> 00:05:28,244
He's mine...

83
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:43,092
Huh? Manager!

84
00:05:44,802 --> 00:05:46,012
Ms. Seri?

85
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:49,349
Hello! Yes, I moved to
this neighborhood.

86
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:50,308
Sorry?

87
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:54,145
Ah, you moved... here.

88
00:05:57,106 --> 00:05:58,858
I think I need to go now...

89
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,234
Then I'll see you on set.

90
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:01,569
Ah, yes. Bye.

91
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:47,080
As expected, night drinks
are best in this weather.

92
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:47,990
Alcohol addiction.

93
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:50,284
Hey, don't call it an addiction.

94
00:06:51,035 --> 00:06:52,864
It's about willpower

95
00:06:53,538 --> 00:06:55,623
and belief, you know.

96
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,626
How was class today?

97
00:07:00,002 --> 00:07:01,546
It was really tough.

98
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,800
Earning someone else's money
is the hardest thing in the world.

99
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:05,800
Look at you.

100
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,136
You've become a faceless citizen.

101
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:10,388
I'm not struggling.

102
00:07:13,891 --> 00:07:15,977
You've mastered
the basics of being a star.

103
00:07:16,769 --> 00:07:18,438
Everyone should learn from you.

104
00:07:20,064 --> 00:07:21,274
Just accept my confession.

105
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:22,525
This is getting old.

106
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:25,069
Don't you ever get tired of this?

107
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:26,863
You're so persistent.

108
00:07:30,741 --> 00:07:32,535
(What's going on between those two?)

109
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:37,792
What are they talking about?

110
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:47,508
Ah, he's so cute.

111
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,512
How can someone be this cute?

112
00:07:57,518 --> 00:08:00,188
That's my guy.

113
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,027
So handsome, as always.

114
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:11,324
As expected,

115
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:14,952
he's glowing.

116
00:08:23,252 --> 00:08:23,794
Saebyeok!

117
00:08:24,962 --> 00:08:26,797
Hello, what brings you here?

118
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:29,008
I live nearby.

119
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:33,471
Really?

120
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:35,765
Okay then.

121
00:08:53,157 --> 00:08:56,077
Hey, what if someone sees us?

122
00:08:57,411 --> 00:08:58,329
(Hand?)

123
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:01,666
(So they are not just friends.)

124
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:20,268
When is Saebyeok coming?

125
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,519
How would I know?

126
00:09:25,314 --> 00:09:26,482
We've closed orders.

127
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:28,150
No boyfriend privilege?

128
00:09:28,608 --> 00:09:30,111
You don't have any privileges at all.

129
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:34,198
Your routine is really getting old.

130
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:37,118
Get out.

131
00:09:37,535 --> 00:09:38,244
You get out.

132
00:09:38,976 --> 00:09:40,128
Saebyeok, what to drink?

133
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:54,840
(Finally coming out.)

134
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:00,910
Have you ever learned Chinese before?

135
00:11:01,869 --> 00:11:02,787
No.

136
00:11:04,864 --> 00:11:06,400
Then this is your first time learning.

137
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:11,087
Then a level test
wouldn't really be necessary...

138
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:12,129
It looks like

139
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:14,173
you have a boyfriend.

140
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:16,258
Sorry?

141
00:11:18,368 --> 00:11:19,679
I noticed you're wearing a ring.

142
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:23,766
Yes.

143
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:27,019
How long have you been together?

144
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:30,439
About two years...

145
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:35,903
He must treat you very well.

146
00:11:38,197 --> 00:11:39,448
Yes, well...

147
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:45,162
We have an afternoon beginner class.
Would you like to try it before deciding?

148
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:46,706
No, I won't register.

149
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:48,708
Sorry?

150
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:51,669
I don't like the teacher.

151
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:53,587
Goodbye.

152
00:12:00,302 --> 00:12:01,887
That's a new kind of rude customer.

153
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:02,972
So annoying.

154
00:12:05,891 --> 00:12:08,227
But don't people usually ask
if I have a girlfriend?

155
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:16,318
Actor Yeo Saebyeok, you're known
as a fashion icon as well.

156
00:12:16,485 --> 00:12:19,447
Do you have a particular style
you usually go for?

157
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:21,574
(What kind of style do you usually go for?)
Rather than a specific style,

158
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:23,826
I just wear what feels comfortable

159
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:25,828
and suits me best.

160
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:31,417
Exactly, it's not easy to know
what suits you best.

161
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:34,170
Do you like wearing accessories as well?

162
00:12:34,336 --> 00:12:37,423
I don't like wearing too many things,
so I usually don't.

163
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,510
But this one means something.

164
00:12:52,521 --> 00:12:53,939
I'll kill him.

165
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:06,368
I'll kill him...

166
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:11,740
Hyung!

167
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:13,300
You know today's birthday party, right?

168
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:15,503
What time do you think
he'll be done today?

169
00:13:16,378 --> 00:13:17,056
Seven?

170
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:19,548
Okay... Eight.

171
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:23,135
Because he's always late
to the time you say.

172
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:30,976
Anyway, don't make any detours.
Bring him straight home.

173
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:31,644
Got it?

174
00:13:32,478 --> 00:13:34,647
Dad and I put a lot of effort
into preparing this.

175
00:14:00,881 --> 00:14:02,091
Thank you.

176
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:03,342
(I liked him first.)

177
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:07,221
Here, please take this.

178
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:08,597
Thank you!

179
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:10,808
I'll support you until the end.

180
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:13,352
(I said we'd be together until the end.)

181
00:14:15,813 --> 00:14:16,605
(Don't smile.)

182
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:19,275
(I said don't smile.)

183
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:21,068
(Don't you two go off)

184
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:22,695
(being happy without me!)

185
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:24,864
Die!

186
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:26,574
Mr. Yeo!

187
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:15,831
Dad?

188
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:42,024
Dad, please get it together. Dad!

189
00:15:42,232 --> 00:15:42,983
Dad!

190
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:44,610
Please wake up!

191
00:15:45,027 --> 00:15:45,694
Dad!

192
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:48,197
Someone please help! Please!

193
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:49,073
Please!

194
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:55,996
(Last night, the father of popular actor
Yeo Saebyeok, Mr. Yeo,)

195
00:15:55,996 --> 00:16:00,084
(was fatally stabbed by an assailant,
but died after being taken to the hospital.)

196
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:15,182
(Maumchae Funeral Hall)

197
00:16:15,265 --> 00:16:16,141
I'm sorry.

198
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:19,648
It's all because of me.

199
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:34,076
(It's your fault!)

200
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:36,286
(He died because of you.)

201
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:38,580
(Gi Haneul.)

202
00:16:39,289 --> 00:16:40,916
(You should have died instead.)

203
00:16:59,935 --> 00:17:00,936
Mom

204
00:17:02,771 --> 00:17:04,732
returned safely to the U.S.

205
00:17:12,656 --> 00:17:13,240
But...

206
00:17:17,312 --> 00:17:18,704
she said she won't be coming back.

207
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:33,552
I'm sorry.

208
00:18:12,466 --> 00:18:13,467
Eat up.

209
00:18:14,134 --> 00:18:15,344
You need to eat to survive.

210
00:18:41,954 --> 00:18:42,913
Saebyeok.

211
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:49,545
Should we leave?

212
00:19:22,202 --> 00:19:23,078
Haneul.

213
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:26,248
Why are you out here alone?

214
00:19:34,756 --> 00:19:35,549
Don't cry.

215
00:19:39,094 --> 00:19:39,803
I'm sorry.

216
00:19:42,472 --> 00:19:43,515
It's all because of me.

217
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:46,935
No, Haneul. It's not.

218
00:19:50,647 --> 00:19:51,690
I'm so scared.

219
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:01,408
I'm no longer
just a happy memory for you.

220
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:04,036
Don't say that.

221
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:07,956
I'll hold you back like a shadow

222
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:11,251
like a shadow forever.

223
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:15,923
I can't survive without you.

224
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:17,841
You know that.

225
00:20:21,762 --> 00:20:24,097
I'll end up ruining everything.

226
00:20:25,766 --> 00:20:26,642
It's okay to ruin it.

227
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:28,320
It's okay to fall apart.

228
00:20:29,519 --> 00:20:30,979
Please, just stay by my side.

229
00:20:34,858 --> 00:20:36,318
But all of this is because of me.

230
00:20:41,824 --> 00:20:43,659
Is it really okay for me
to be by your side?

231
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:50,123
Please don't leave me alone.

232
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,544
Now I really have no one.

233
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:00,467
Let's live.

234
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,053
Let's live together.

235
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:12,271
(Yeah.)

236
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:14,481
(Let's live)

237
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:16,275
(together.)

238
00:21:40,549 --> 00:21:41,341
I love you.

239
00:21:45,762 --> 00:21:46,888
I love you.

240
00:23:11,973 --> 00:23:13,392
(To Actor Saebyeok)

241
00:23:28,865 --> 00:23:33,912
(It's been a while. I really should
have killed Gi Haneul after all)

242
00:24:43,064 --> 00:24:43,607
Haneul.

243
00:24:52,192 --> 00:24:53,024
Why hide it from me?

244
00:24:53,533 --> 00:24:54,576
Let me explain.

245
00:24:58,455 --> 00:24:58,997
Explain what?

246
00:25:00,916 --> 00:25:02,751
You've always treated me like an idiot.

247
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:04,628
What is there to explain now?

248
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:06,129
I did it all for you.

249
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:08,340
For me?

250
00:25:10,217 --> 00:25:12,677
You decided to shoulder
all the pain alone for my sake?

251
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,776
What kind of ridiculous
responsibility is that?

252
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:19,309
Every time you got hurt,
it felt like I was dying instead.

253
00:25:21,186 --> 00:25:24,981
I thought if I took it instead,
you'd hurt a little less.

254
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:25,982
Liar.

255
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:30,111
You're just afraid.

256
00:25:32,155 --> 00:25:33,615
You're afraid

257
00:25:34,741 --> 00:25:35,968
of being alone again.

258
00:25:35,968 --> 00:25:36,576
Haneul.

259
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:37,160
You

260
00:25:38,912 --> 00:25:41,122
never trusted me even once.

261
00:25:41,164 --> 00:25:42,499
It's... It's all my fault.

262
00:25:46,461 --> 00:25:48,630
I never expected that anyway.

263
00:25:49,673 --> 00:25:50,882
It's all because of you.

264
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:57,889
Saebyeok.

265
00:26:01,435 --> 00:26:01,935
I...

266
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,024
I really have no confidence left.

267
00:26:07,774 --> 00:26:09,734
How much more do I have to push you

268
00:26:10,624 --> 00:26:12,112
for this to end?

269
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:19,077
Saebyeok, I'm so scared.

270
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:25,208
I'm terrified that one day

271
00:26:25,709 --> 00:26:26,960
you might actually die.

272
00:26:32,966 --> 00:26:33,883
Let's break up.

273
00:26:34,175 --> 00:26:34,718
Seriously.

274
00:26:36,469 --> 00:26:37,345
Please.

275
00:26:39,889 --> 00:26:40,724
Gi Haneul.

276
00:26:44,769 --> 00:26:45,937
Let's break up.

277
00:27:10,712 --> 00:27:11,880
(Han Jeongyun.)

278
00:27:20,263 --> 00:27:21,931
(There's something
you need to do for me.)

279
00:27:24,809 --> 00:27:26,186
Kill Gi Haneul for me.

280
00:27:28,855 --> 00:27:30,690
Yeah? Got it.

281
00:27:31,358 --> 00:27:32,942
Someone died because of him.

282
00:27:33,952 --> 00:27:35,552
Does it make sense for him to live well?

283
00:27:36,237 --> 00:27:37,614
The reason I'm here

284
00:27:38,073 --> 00:27:39,324
is all because of Gi Haneul.

285
00:27:40,992 --> 00:27:43,411
Your only family ended up like this
because of that punk.

286
00:27:44,913 --> 00:27:45,413
You'll...

287
00:27:46,748 --> 00:27:47,749
do this for me, right?

288
00:27:49,459 --> 00:27:51,795
Don't worry. I'm your brother.

289
00:27:52,796 --> 00:27:53,838
I'll kill him for you.

290
00:27:59,010 --> 00:28:00,220
Mr. Yoon Junghan?

291
00:28:01,429 --> 00:28:03,181
You don't seem to have
any cafe experience.

292
00:28:05,809 --> 00:28:07,477
I pick things up quickly.

293
00:28:33,753 --> 00:28:36,214
(As the saying goes,)

294
00:28:46,349 --> 00:28:49,728
(fate makes us pass by each other.)

295
00:28:56,234 --> 00:28:57,110
(But)

296
00:28:57,736 --> 00:28:59,446
(there's also a saying...)

297
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,994
(It's better never)

298
00:29:06,870 --> 00:29:07,662
(to have met.)

299
00:29:11,499 --> 00:29:14,669
(Have you received
any threatening letters from Lee Seri?)

300
00:29:18,298 --> 00:29:21,217
- (Threatening... letters?)
- (Yeah.)

301
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:42,280
(The murderer is you, Gi Haneul)

302
00:30:06,513 --> 00:30:08,681
(It's better never)

303
00:30:09,098 --> 00:30:10,099
(to have met.)

304
00:30:44,342 --> 00:30:50,265
(No matter where you are,
I would've found you in the end.)

305
00:31:09,210 --> 00:31:12,247
♪The more I try to run away♪

306
00:31:12,545 --> 00:31:14,228
♪The clearer it becomes♪

307
00:31:15,830 --> 00:31:19,120
♪Even the word "love"♪

308
00:31:19,416 --> 00:31:20,607
♪Can't convey how I feel♪

309
00:31:22,676 --> 00:31:25,749
♪Watching your shadow moving forward♪

310
00:31:25,978 --> 00:31:27,610
♪Sometimes, I resent you♪

311
00:31:27,610 --> 00:31:29,376
♪But without you,
everything feels strange♪

312
00:31:29,701 --> 00:31:34,771
♪The pain also makes me grow♪

313
00:31:36,218 --> 00:31:38,118
♪There is a lot to say♪

314
00:31:38,118 --> 00:31:39,538
♪Trying to separate us♪

315
00:31:39,851 --> 00:31:42,696
♪Even if I look like a fool♪

316
00:31:43,292 --> 00:31:44,812
♪It doesn't matter♪

317
00:31:44,812 --> 00:31:46,778
♪This is how we are♪

318
00:31:46,778 --> 00:31:49,693
♪Connected to each other♪

319
00:31:49,754 --> 00:31:53,273
♪We are truly strange♪

320
00:31:53,754 --> 00:31:56,805
♪Pushing each other away,
yet embracing again♪

321
00:31:56,805 --> 00:31:59,098
♪Between love and pain♪

322
00:31:59,130 --> 00:32:02,141
♪In some corner♪

323
00:32:02,292 --> 00:32:05,777
♪In the end, we can only be together♪

324
00:32:12,884 --> 00:32:16,716
♪Because that's us♪

325
00:32:20,170 --> 00:32:21,530
♪Even if what we said yesterday♪

326
00:32:21,530 --> 00:32:22,984
♪Remains in the heart♪

327
00:32:23,162 --> 00:32:24,954
♪As time passes♪

328
00:32:24,954 --> 00:32:26,170
♪Maybe I'll laugh about it♪

329
00:32:26,170 --> 00:32:28,250
♪Even those painful memories♪

330
00:32:28,250 --> 00:32:29,370
♪Are also ours♪

331
00:32:29,524 --> 00:32:32,104
♪Seems we can♪

332
00:32:32,104 --> 00:32:34,041
♪Be more understanding♪

333
00:32:34,516 --> 00:32:36,700
♪I clearly told myself♪

334
00:32:37,722 --> 00:32:39,980
♪Never to see you again♪

335
00:32:40,218 --> 00:32:42,927
♪But hearing your voice♪

336
00:32:43,284 --> 00:32:44,314
♪I completely break down♪
